{
    "story": {
        "title": "🃏 Texas Hold'em River Math",
        "html": "<p><b>The scenario:</b> You are at the final table in the World Series of Poker. The game is of imperfect information: you know your cards, but not theirs.</p><p><b>1. Inspect the Math:</b> Click <i>Win Probability (Showdown)</i>. Initially, you have a solid 52% chance of winning.</p><p><b>2. The Opponent Bets:</b> Now click <i>Opponent Action (Flop)</i> and observe them by pinning the variable to '<b>Aggressive Bet/Raise</b>'.</p><p><b>3. Watch the Inference:</b> The network instantly recalculates. By betting aggressively, the backend infers a massive spike in their hand strength, plunging your mathematical Win Probability down to 23%! Always fold bad odds.</p>"
    },
